# Personal Blog Project Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 personal blog with App Router, Tailwind CSS, and Markdown content management.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- React 18
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Markdown (via unified/remark/rehype)

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports for components
- Use Tailwind CSS classes instead of custom CSS
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions

## File Structure
- `app/` - Next.js pages and routes
- `components/` - Reusable React components
- `lib/` - Utility functions and helpers
- `content/` - Markdown blog posts
- `public/` - Static assets

## Component Guidelines
- Keep components small and focused
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Add proper accessibility attributes
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Follow the paper-card design system
- Maintain consistent spacing (use Tailwind spacing scale)
- Ensure responsive design (mobile-first)

## Content Guidelines
- All blog posts in `content/` directory
- Use YAML frontmatter for metadata
- Required fields: title, date, excerpt
- Optional fields: tags, language, author, image

## SEO Requirements
- Add metadata to all pages
- Use semantic HTML
- Include alt text for images
- Generate sitemap and RSS feed

## Performance
- Use next/image for images
- Implement proper caching
- Minimize client-side JavaScript
- Use static generation when possible

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML
- Add ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain color contrast ratios

